<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Paul Gascoigne's management has hinted that the football star is joining the Italian version of Strictly Come Dancing.</p>

<p>M &amp; N Management took to Twitter on Monday night to share a video of Gascoigne, 53, known as his moniker Gazza, dancing while cooking apple crumble in the kitchen. </p>

<p>They captioned the clip with: 'Someone is practising their dance moves ahead of Ballando con Le stelle.'</p>

<p>Exciting: Paul Gascoigne's management has hinted that the football star is joining the Italian version of Strictly Come Dancing </p>

<p>They cryptically added the hashtags: '#dancingwiththestars #lazio #italian #gazza #MondayMotivation #celebritynews.'</p>

<p>Ballando Con Le Stelle, which translates to Dance With The Stars, is a spin-off the hit BBC One series Strictly Come Dancing.</p>

<p>In the video, which has had 13.3K views, Gascoigne is making an apple crumble as he starts singing and dancing to Oliver!'s Consider Yourself. </p>

<p>Just last week, M &amp; N Management tweeted a picture of Gascoigne in a neon yellow jacket and grey shorts as they revealed he had been training.</p>

<p>Fun: Ballando Con Le Stelle, which translates to Dance With The Stars, is a spin-off the hit BBC One series Strictly Come Dancing (2019 winners Lasse Matberg and Sara Di Vaira pictured) </p>

<p>Having fun: M &amp; N Management took to Twitter on Monday night to share a video of Gascoigne, 53, known as his moniker Gazza, dancing to Oliver!'s Consider Yourself while cooking apple crumble in the kitchen </p>

<p>They tweeted: 'When all else fails, train in a luminous coat #gazza #paulgascoigne #SaturdayMorning #training #celebritynews #showbiz #celebrity #RangersFC #englandfc #TottenhamHotspur.'</p>

<p>In January, Gascoigne revealed he is the happiest he has been for 'years' after spending £20,000 to have anti-boozing pellets puts into his stomach to stop him drinking.   </p>

<p>The former England star has blown his £20million fortune from his playing career and gone in and out of rehab because of alcohol-related problems since retiring.</p>

<p>Twitter users were quick to comment on the video shared by M &amp; N Management and point out how well the footballing legend looked.</p>

<p>Training: Just last week, M &amp; N Management tweeted a picture of Gascoigne in a neon yellow jacket and grey shorts as they revealed he had been training</p>

<p>They tweeted: 'When all else fails, train in a luminous coat #gazza #paulgascoigne #SaturdayMorning #training #celebritynews #showbiz #celebrity #RangersFC #englandfc #TottenhamHotspur.'</p>

<p>One person said: 'Great to see him looking so good guys' followed by a thumbs up emoji.  </p>

<p>A different user commented: 'Great to see Gazza happy and looking good.' </p>

<p>While a different fan added: 'Great to see Gazza looking well and happy.'</p>

<p>Earlier this year, Gascoigne revealed he had been offered a spot on the Italian dance show and was deciding whether to take it. </p>

<p>The sporting star, who played for Rome's Lazio club from 1992 to 1995, told the Mirror: 'They still love me because of my time playing there so I may give it a go.'</p>

<p>Support: Twitter users were quick to comment on the video shared by M &amp; N Management and point out how well the footballing legend looked </p>

<p>Plans: Earlier this year, Gascoigne revealed he had been offered a spot on the Italian dance show and was deciding whether to take it (2019 show still) </p>

<p>While his agent, Katie Davies, told the publication: 'It is a very long show in Italy. It runs for about four hours. So we will have to look at how we would do it. We don’t know if it would be for a full stint, or a shorter format.'</p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted Gascoigne's representatives for comment.</p>

<p>It's been an exciting year for the sporting star and earlier this month he was reportedly left 'over the moon' after learning he's set to become a grandfather for the first time.</p>

<p>The former England star learnt that his stepson Mason, 30, is expecting his first child with partner Jaimee Wyatt after his stepdaughter Bianca shared the news with fans on Instagram.</p>

<p>Surprise! It's been an exciting year for the sporting star and earlier this month he was reportedly left 'over the moon' after learning he's set to become a grandfather for the first time (stepchildren Mason, 30, left, and Bianca, 33, right, pictured)  </p>

<p>Paul is stepdad to Mason and Bianca, and also shares son Regan, 24, with his ex-wife Sheryl.</p>

<p>Bianca let slip the news when she shared a snap with her brother, writing: 'I'm gonna be an Auntie! My brother Mase is having a baby!!' </p>

<p>A source told The Sun on Sunday: 'Gazza is over the moon. It’s just the bit of good news he needs. He can’t wait to be a grandad.'</p>

<p>Parents! Mason's partner Jaimee Wyatt revealed their impending arrival on Facebook, gushing they 'couldn't be any happier'</p>

<p>According to the publication, Mason's partner Jaimee shared the news with fans on Instagram, writing: 'Couldn't be any more happier. We are having a healthy beautiful baby.'</p>

<p>MailOnline contacted representatives for Paul Gascoigne for further comment at the time. </p>

<p>It came after Paul was left devastated when thieves broke into his flat and stole £140,000 worth of jewellery, after Piers Morgan shared a snap of him at a recording of his ITV series Life Stories.  </p>

<p>Among the items stolen were treasures belonging to his late father, which the sporting star told the Sunday People 'meant so much to him.'   </p>

<p>The raiders' haul included a £2,000 gold cigar cutter and watch both owned by his late father John, according to the Mirror.  </p>

<p>They also took a £40,000 gold diamond-encrusted watch bought with his first pay cheque from Tottenham and a Championship medal from Glasgow Rangers.</p>

<p>Gascoigne went to London to support lifelong friend Vinnie Jones, 55, while he filmed his Life Stories chat. </p>

<p>Piers told the Sunday People he was 'sorry to hear' about the burglary and said the least he can do is 'buy him some new steaks.'</p>

<p>Scary: It came after Paul was left devastated when thieves broke into his Dorset flat and stole £140,000 worth of jewellery </p>
